# CLI Module

The {{ project_name }} CLI provides a command-line interface built with [Typer](https://typer.tiangolo.com/).

## Installation

```bash
uv sync --group cli
```

## Usage

```bash
uv run {{ project_slug }} --help
# or: uv run python -m {{ package_name }}.cli --help
```

## Commands

Core commands include `quickstart`, `version`, `init`, `list`, `config`, and `plugin`.
Plugin commands (for example `demo`) are registered via entry points.

### `version`

```bash
uv run {{ project_slug }} version
uv run {{ project_slug }} version --short
```

### `config`

```bash
uv run {{ project_slug }} config set app.name "my-app"
uv run {{ project_slug }} config get app.name
uv run {{ project_slug }} config list
```

## Configuration

1. **Environment variables**: prefixed with `{{ package_name | upper }}_`
2. **Config file**: `config.toml` or `.{{ package_name }}.toml`
3. **Command-line arguments**: highest precedence

### Example Configuration

```toml
# config.toml
[app]
name = "{{ project_name }}"
verbose = true
log_level = "INFO"
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `{{ package_name | upper }}_VERBOSE` | Enable verbose output | `false` |
| `{{ package_name | upper }}_LOG_LEVEL` | Log level | `INFO` |
